author: stefan2
msg: Optimize membuffer cache index layout.  Groups should have a power
of two size to make them align properly with memory pages etc.
As part of this, factor out a group header struct which will be
extended soon.
* subversion/libsvn_subr/cache-membuffer.c
(entry_t): 32 bits are enough for cache item sizes
(group_header_t): new struct factored out from entry_group_t
(GROUP_BLOCK_SIZE): new constant
(GROUP_SIZE): move down and define depending on GROUP_BLOCK_SIZE
(entry_group_t): use header and padding
(drop_entry,
insert_entry,
initialize_group,
find_entry,
svn_membuffer_get_segment_info): update entry_group_t users
